#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 3. Tatiyavagga → māravaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn4.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Māra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Sambahulasutta "
msgstr "21. Several "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.118, pts2ed1.259, sc1
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati silāvatiyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans near Silāvatī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: This passage exposes how poor “dwelling” is as a rendering of viharati in such cases.
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavato avidūre appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharanti. "
msgstr "Now at that time several mendicants were meditating not far from the Buddha, diligent, keen, and resolute. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā brāhmaṇavaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā mahantena jaṭaṇḍuvena ajinakkhipanivattho jiṇṇo gopānasivaṅko ghurughurupassāsī udumbaradaṇḍaṃ gahetvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked manifested in the form of a brahmin with a large matted dreadlock, wearing an antelope hide. He was old, bent double, wheezing, and held a staff made of cluster fig tree wood. He went up to those mendicants and said, "

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.5"
msgid "“daharā bhavanto pabbajitā susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikkīḷitāvino kāmesu. "
msgstr "“You’ve gone forth while young, reverends. You’re black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life, and you’ve never flirted with sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.6"
msgid "Bhuñjantu bhavanto mānusake kāme. "
msgstr "Enjoy human sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.7"
msgid "Mā sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvitthā”ti. "
msgstr "Don’t give up what is visible in the present to chase after what takes effect over time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.8"
msgid "“Na kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvāma. "
msgstr "“Brahmin, that’s not what we’re doing. "

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.9"
msgid "Kālikañca kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hitvā sandiṭṭhikaṃ anudhāvāma. "
msgstr "We’re giving up what takes effect over time to chase after what is visible in the present. "

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.10"
msgid "Kālikā hi, brāhmaṇa, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "For the Buddha says that sensual pleasures take effect over time; they give much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks. "

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.11"
msgid "Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "But this teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.12"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, māro pāpimā sīsaṃ okampetvā jivhaṃ nillāletvā tivisākhaṃ nalāṭe nalāṭikaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā daṇḍamolubbha pakkāmi. "
msgstr "When they had spoken, Māra the Wicked shook his head, waggled his tongue, raised his eyebrows until his brow puckered in three furrows, and departed leaning on his staff. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.261, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.21:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those senior mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said, "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.2"
msgid "“idha mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato avidūre appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharāma. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, aññataro brāhmaṇo mahantena jaṭaṇḍuvena ajinakkhipanivattho jiṇṇo gopānasivaṅko ghurughurupassāsī udumbaradaṇḍaṃ gahetvā yena mayaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā amhe etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.4"
msgid "‘daharā bhavanto pabbajitā susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikkīḷitāvino kāmesu. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.5"
msgid "Bhuñjantu bhavanto mānusake kāme. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.6"
msgid "Mā sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvitthā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, mayaṃ, bhante, taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocumha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.8"
msgid "‘na kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvāma. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.9"
msgid "Kālikañca kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hitvā sandiṭṭhikaṃ anudhāvāma. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.10"
msgid "Kālikā hi, brāhmaṇa, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.11"
msgid "Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.12"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, so brāhmaṇo sīsaṃ okampetvā jivhaṃ nillāletvā tivisākhaṃ nalāṭe nalāṭikaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā daṇḍamolubbha pakkanto”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.21:3.1"
msgid "“Neso, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇo. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, that was no brahmin. "

msgctxt "sn4.21:3.2"
msgid "Māro eso pāpimā tumhākaṃ vicakkhukammāya āgato”ti. "
msgstr "That was Māra the Wicked who came to pull the wool over your eyes!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.21:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.262, sc4
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.1"
msgid "“Yo dukkhamaddakkhi yatonidānaṃ, "
msgstr "“When a person has seen where suffering comes from "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.2"
msgid "Kāmesu so jantu kathaṃ nameyya; "
msgstr "how could they incline towards sensual pleasures? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.3"
msgid "Upadhiṃ viditvā saṅgoti loke, "
msgstr "Realizing that attachment is a tie in the world, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.4"
msgid "Tasseva jantu vinayāya sikkhe”ti. "
msgstr "a person would train to remove it.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
